In a mixing bowl, combine flour, salt and sugar; cut in butter until mixture resembles cornmeal. Mix egg and milk; add to flour mixture. Pat into a greased 13-in. x 9-in. x 2-in. baking pan. Arrange fruit on crust. Combine remaining filling ingredients; pour over fruit. For topping, combine ingredients until crumbly; sprinkle over filling. Bake at 350 degrees F for 50-60 minutes.